e, Bourgogne, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1115–1191":"1115–1191","1101–1175":"1101–1175","1122–1204":"1122–1204","1140–Male":"1140–Deceased","1141–1217":"1141–1217","1146–Male":"1146–Deceased","1081–1140":"1081–1140","1087–1114":"1087–1114","1087":"1087","1175":"1175","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1191":"1191","1081":"1081","1217":"1217","1139":"1139","ABT 1140":"1140","1204":"1204","1115":"1115","1114":"1114","1146":"1146","1101":"1101","1122":"1122","França":"France","Châtel-Censoir, Avallon, Yonne, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Châtel-Censoir, Yonne, Burgundy, France","Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, France":"Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France","Châtel-Censoir, Yonne, Bourgogne, France":"Châtel-Censoir, Yonne, Burgundy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Vergy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>verge</i> ‘rod, pole, or perch (unit of length or area); half-acre’ (Old French <i>verge</i>), perhaps denoting the owner of that amount of land.","English: variant of <b>Ferridge</b>, a habitational name from Verridge Wood in Frant (Sussex). The placename probably derives from Old English <i>fearn</i> ‘fern, bracken’ + <i>hrycg</i> ‘ridge’.","Catalan (<b>Vergé</b>): variant of <b>Verger</b>, a topographic name from Catalan <i>verger</i> ‘orchard’ (from Latin <i>viridiarium</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Thivierge","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Armand, Henri, Hermel, Lucien, Herve, Renald, Rosaire.","French: variant of <b>Thibierge</b> (and, in North America, an altered form of this), which is of the same origin as <b>Théberge</b> (see   Theberge  ). The surname <i>Thivierge</i> is very rare in France. Compare   Verge  .","History: Hippolyte Thibierge from Blois in Loir-et-Cher, France, married Renée Hervet in Blois in 1653, died in Sainte-Famille, Île d'Orléans, QC, in 1700. His descendants also bear another altered form of the surname, <i>Verge</i>."]},{"name":"Verges","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Raul, Carmelita, Gilberto, Jorge, Jose, Juanita, Lourdes, Nieves, Rafael, Ricardo, Vidal.  French Emile.","French (Occitan; <b>Vergès</b>) and Catalan (<b>Vergés</b>): from the plural of Occitan <i>verg(i)èr</i> and Catalan <i>verger</i> ‘orchard’, a topographic name for someone who lived near an orchard or garden, or an occupational name for someone who was employed in one (see   Verge   3 and   Verdier   2)."]}]},{"name":"Guy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of a compound name starting with <i>witu</i> ‘wood’ or <i>wīt</i> ‘wide’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England. In Old French initial <i>w-</i> regularly became <i>gu-</i>. The usual Norman forms of the name were <i>Gy</i> or <i>Guido</i>. In medieval Latin the same name is found as <i>Wido</i>. It was a popular name among the Normans, enhanced no doubt by the romance of Guy of Warwick, recounting the exploits of a folk hero of the Crusades."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guy de Vergy was born in 1115, his father, Simon de Vergy, was 34 and his mother, Ermengarde Elisabeth DE FOUVENT, was 28. He married Adélaïs de Beaumont-sur-Vingeanne in 1139, in Châtel-Censoir, Yonne, Burgundy, France. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1191, at the age of 76."},"et":{"1115–1191":"1115–1191","1101–1175":"1101–1175","1122–1204":"1122–1204","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1141–1217":"1141–1217","1146–Male":"1146–Surnud","1081–1140":"1081–1140","1087–1114":"1087–1114","1087":"1087","1175":"1175","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1191":"1191","1081":"1081","1217":"1217","1139":"1139","ABT 1140":"1140","1204":"1204","1115":"1115","1114":"1114","1146":"1146","1101":"1101","1122":"1122","França":"Prantsusmaa","Châtel-Censoir, Avallon, Yonne, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Châtel-Censoir, Yonne, Bourgogne, Prantsusmaa","Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, France":"Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, Prantsusmaa","Châtel-Censoir, Yonne, Bourgogne, France":"Châtel-Censoir, Yonne, Bourgogne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1115–1191":"1115–1191","1101–1175":"1101–1175","1122–1204":"1122–1204","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1141–1217":"1141–1217","1146–Male":"1146–Kuollut","1081–1140":"1081–1140","1087–1114":"1087–1114","1087":"1087","1175":"1175","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1191":"1191","1081":"1081","1217":"1217","1139":"1139","ABT 1140":"1140","1204":"1204","1115":"1115","1114":"1114","1146":"1146","1101":"1101","1122":"1122","França":"Ranska","Châtel-Censoir, Avallon, Yonne, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Châtel-Censoir, Yonne, Bourgogne, Ranska","Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, France":"Reulle-Vergy, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, Ranska","Châtel-Censoir, Yonne, Bourgogne, France":"Châtel-Censoir, Yonne, Bourgogne, Ranska"},"fr":{"1115–1191":"1115–1191","1101–1175":"1101–1175","1122–1204":"1122–1204","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1141–1217":"1141–1217","1146–Male":"1146–Décédé","1081–1140":"1081–1140","1087–1114":"1087–1114","1087":"1087","1175":"1175","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1191":"1191","1081":"1081","1217":"1217","11